An avalanche crashed through a small Austrian resort on Tuesdaykilling at least eight people and leaving dozens missingin what officials feared could turn out to be Austria's worst snow disaster in years.
A new avalanche 45-feet deep thundered down the mountainside outside the stricken village of Galtuer todayburying 10 people in its paththe Austria Press Agency reported.
At least eight people have been confirmed killed and 30 others injured as two avalanches roared through a ski resort in Austria's western state of Triol on Tuesday eveningthe Austrian news media reported.
